00:24:19,542 --> 00:24:22,879
他们没有理由这么做。你让他们破产了。
They got no reason to be. You put them out of business.

286
00:24:22,963 --> 00:24:25,298
伙计，那边有很多好酒。
Man, they got plenty good liquor over yonder.

287
00:24:25,382 --> 00:24:26,925
我自己喝。
I'll drink my own.

288
00:24:31,638 --> 00:24:37,644
你刚来的时候，我承认我们这些老家伙有点冷淡。
Now when you first came here, I'll admit that us old-timers were a bit standoffish.

289
00:24:37,727 --> 00:24:40,605
一开始我们不太了解你。
We didn't know you all that well at first.

290
00:24:40,689 --> 00:24:45,652
自然地，一件事对某些人有利，对另一些人却无益。
Naturally, a thing is profitable to some is unprofitable to others.

291
00:24:45,735 --> 00:24:50,490
就像那家伙说的，一个人的美食可能是另一个人的毒药。
As the fella says, one man's meat is another man's poison.

292
00:24:50,573 --> 00:25:02,043
我们都知道，在某种程度上，由于这个人在辛迪加种植园的成功，这里的一些人在经济上遭受了损失，但作为一个整体，社区将获得丰厚的利润。
We all know that some folks here have suffered financially due in some measure to this man's success with his Syndicate Plantation, but as a whole, the community stands to reap a nice fat profit.

293
00:25:02,127 --> 00:25:05,338
嘿，参议员，下次为共和党竞选吧。
Hey, senator, next time run on a Republican ticket.

294
00:25:05,422 --> 00:25:07,590
我们会帮你争取到黑鬼的选票。
We'll get the nigger vote out for you.

295
00:25:11,261 --> 00:25:13,763
-席尔瓦!席尔瓦先生!——火!
- Silva! Mr. Silva! - Fire!

296
00:25:13,847 --> 00:25:16,141
-席尔瓦先生!-席尔瓦!席尔瓦先生!
- Mr. Silva! - Silva! Mr. Silva!

297
00:25:22,147 --> 00:25:24,774
-席尔瓦!席尔瓦先生!-席尔瓦!
- Silva! Mr. Silva! - Silva!

298
00:25:35,869 --> 00:25:38,204
把马车挪开!移动它们!
Move the wagons! Move them!

299
00:25:38,288 --> 00:25:40,457
让棉花动起来!摇滚!
Get that cotton moving! Rock!

300
00:25:45,670 --> 00:25:49,174
罗克，让棉花动起来!把马车弄出来!
Rock, get the cotton moving! Get those wagons out!

301
00:25:49,257 --> 00:25:52,010
席尔瓦先生，你在哪里?
Mr. Silva, where are you?

302
00:26:26,795 --> 00:26:28,755
煤油。
Kerosene can.

303
00:26:50,777 --> 00:26:54,239
好吧，法警，你打算怎么找到那个烧了我杜松子酒的人?
Alright, marshal, what you gonna do about finding the man that burned down my gin?

304
00:26:54,322 --> 00:26:57,200
你凭什么确定你的杜松子酒被人放火烧了?
Well, what makes you so sure your gin was set fire to?

305
00:26:57,283 --> 00:26:59,786
哦，看看周围。
Oh, look around.

306
00:26:59,869 --> 00:27:02,789
你见过这么多快乐的脸吗?
Did you ever see so many happy faces?

307
00:27:02,872 --> 00:27:06,417
这看起来像一个富人的葬礼，他所有的亲戚都参加了。
It looks like a rich man's funeral with all his relations attending.

308
00:27:06,501 --> 00:27:08,211
我可不想证明这一点。
I'd hate to have to prove that.

309
00:27:08,294 --> 00:27:10,755
我可不想靠你来证明。
I'd hate to have to depend on you to prove it.

310
00:27:13,341 --> 00:27:15,009
我真的无法想象。
I can't honestly imagine.

311
00:27:15,093 --> 00:27:16,529
如果是纵火案，是谁干的?
If it's a case of arson, who done it?

312
00:27:16,553 --> 00:27:20,469
大火发生的时候，所有被你弄丢生意的人都在那辆杜松子酒里。
Every poor man you put out of business was right there in that gin when the fire broke out.

313
00:27:20,515 --> 00:27:22,600
一个不是。我知道有一个不是。
One wasn't. I know of one that wasn't.

314
00:27:22,684 --> 00:27:25,520
孩子，说出听起来可疑的名字是件冒险的事。
Boy, namin' names that sounds suspicious is risky business.

315
00:27:25,603 --> 00:27:29,732
我没有指名道姓。但看起来凶手忘记把这个带走了。
I didn't name a name. But looks like whoever did it forgot to take this with him.

316
00:27:29,816 --> 00:27:34,904
法警，作为你的副手，我会拿走这个罐子仔细检查。
Marshal, as your deputy, I'll take this can and I'll examine it very carefully.

317
00:27:34,988 --> 00:27:38,700
看看有没有证据证明这是用来纵火的。
See if there's any basis for thinking it was used for starting a fire.

318
00:27:38,783 --> 00:27:41,953
为了得到这个易拉罐，我不惜血本，我一定要留下它。
I had to run through fire to get this can and I mean to keep it.

319
00:27:42,036 --> 00:27:44,247
把它锁在皮卡车里。
Lock it in the pickup truck.

320
00:27:56,759 --> 00:27:59,095
嘿，吉娜，给我们唱首歌。
Hey, Gina, sing us a song.

321
00:28:01,222 --> 00:28:04,058
我不会的
* I shall not *

322
00:28:04,142 --> 00:28:06,853
我不会被感动的
* I shall not be moved *

323
00:28:06,936 --> 00:28:10,106
我不会的
* I shall not *

324
00:28:10,190 --> 00:28:14,235
我不会像树一样被移动
* I shall not be moved like a tree *

325
00:28:14,319 --> 00:28:18,656
那是种在水边的
* That's planted by the water *

326
00:28:18,740 --> 00:28:22,493
我不会被感动的……＊
* I shall not be moved... *

327
00:28:22,577 --> 00:28:26,414
你打算怎么把剩下的棉花轧出来?
Hey, what you gonna do about ginning out the rest of your cotton?

328
00:28:26,497 --> 00:28:29,375
我用卡车把它运到日落街。
I'll truck it over to Sunset.

329
00:28:29,459 --> 00:28:32,545
柯林斯会帮我弄清楚的。
Collins will gin it out for me.

330
00:28:32,629 --> 00:28:34,464
柯林斯有自己的棉花，伙计。
Collins got his own cotton to gin, fella.

331
00:28:34,547 --> 00:28:37,008
那我就把它运到玻利瓦尔县。
Well, then I'll truck it over to Bolivar county.

332
00:28:37,091 --> 00:28:39,552
这里没人会帮我找借口的。
Ain't nobody around here's gonna gin it out for me.

333
00:28:39,636 --> 00:28:43,598
我不会被感动的
* I shall not be moved *

334
00:28:43,681 --> 00:28:46,559
*每条路线都走得更高?＊
* Every route go higher? *

335
00:28:46,643 --> 00:28:48,269
席尔瓦!
Silva!

336
00:28:53,149 --> 00:28:57,195
——摇滚!-滚开…摇滚，不，不，这是…是我，洛克。
- Rock! - Get off... Rock, no, no, it's... it's me, Rock.

337
00:28:57,278 --> 00:28:59,155
-他们有罐子，老大——什么?什么?
- Oh, they got the can, boss. - What? What?

338
00:28:59,239 --> 00:29:00,448
——谁?谁?-我不知道。
- Who? Who? - I don't know.

339
00:29:00,531 --> 00:29:02,992
肯定是某个人。从后面猛扑过来。
It was somebody. Jumped me from the rear.

340
00:29:06,246 --> 00:29:08,498
退后，退后。
Just stay back, stay back.

341
00:29:11,584 --> 00:29:17,423
孩子，听我这个土生土长的老前辈的建议吧。
Boy, take the advice of an old-timer who was born and raised in this county.

342
00:29:17,507 --> 00:29:24,305
认识方圆五十英里内的每一个黑鬼，每一条猎犬每一个毒菌和每一个树桩。
Knows every nigger, every hound dog every toadstool and every tree stump for 50 miles around here.

343
00:29:24,389 --> 00:29:27,392
我劝你不要再无理取闹了。
My advice is for you not to make any more reckless charges.

344
00:29:27,475 --> 00:29:34,357
当然，作为一个外国人，你已经被一振和二振了……我不需要建议，不需要法律，不需要法庭。
Of course, you being a foreigner, you already got strike one and strike two... I want no advice, no law and no court in this county.

345
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:40,321
我来自一个非常古老的国家，那里的传统是每个人都要做出自己的判断。
I come from a very old country where it's tradition for each man to make his own justice.

346
00:29:40,405 --> 00:29:44,325
就像私酿的酒，私密，秘密。
Like bootlegged liquor, private, in secret.

347
00:29:44,409 --> 00:29:46,995
因为那里也有腐败。
Because there was corruption there too.

348
00:29:47,078 --> 00:29:52,750
如果正义被执行，那也是由每个人自己单独执行的。
And if justice was executed, it was executed by each man himself, alone.

349
00:29:52,834 --> 00:29:54,961
我指的是圣经中的正义。
I mean biblical justice.

350
00:29:55,044 --> 00:29:58,464
以眼还眼，以牙还牙。
Eye for eye, tooth for tooth.

351
00:29:58,548 --> 00:30:00,508
走吧，洛克。
Let's go, Rock.

352
00:30:19,527 --> 00:30:22,238
不要注意这个。我必须这么做。
Don't notice this. I got to.

353
00:30:22,322 --> 00:30:24,365
我什么也没注意到。
I hadn't noticed a thing.

354
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:33,166
-是谁干的，洛克?-你知道的。
- Which one did it, Rock? - You know.

355
00:30:33,249 --> 00:30:36,377
他们都在小屋里，除了一个。
They were all there in the shed, all except one.

356
00:30:36,461 --> 00:30:39,005
不在场的那个，我以为是他干的。
The one who wasn't there, I figured he did it.

357
00:30:42,425 --> 00:30:45,053
他是帮我榨棉花的人。
Well, he's the one who's gonna gin out my cotton.

358
00:31:13,039 --> 00:31:14,540
扶她起来。
Get her up.

359
00:31:21,923 --> 00:31:24,008
家具今天要搬回来。
The furniture's coming back today.

360
00:31:24,092 --> 00:31:26,552
-发发慈悲吧。-快，快，快。
- Have mercy. - Come on, get, get.

361
00:31:35,478 --> 00:31:37,271
什么也别说。
Don't say a word.

362
00:31:37,355 --> 00:31:43,694
有只小鸟已经告诉我你会把那几车棉花直接送到我家门口我想让你知道，你是个非常幸运的家伙。
A little bird already told me that you'd be bringing those wagons full of cotton straight to my door and I want you to know that you're a very lucky fella.

363
00:31:43,778 --> 00:31:44,778
如何来吗?
How come?

364
00:31:44,821 --> 00:31:49,409
我的意思是，我可以保留其他订单，给你优先权。
I mean that I'm in a position to hold back the other orders and give you a priority.

365
00:31:49,492 --> 00:31:51,136
好吧，来吧。快点，从卡车里出来。
Well, come on. Come on, get out of that truck.

366
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:53,097
-和我一起喝杯咖啡。-你的价格是多少?
- And have some coffee with me. - What's your price?

367
00:31:53,121 --> 00:31:54,997
现在你记得我的价格了。它没有改变。
Now you remember my price. It hasn't changed.

368
00:31:55,081 --> 00:31:56,683
你的设备怎么样?这一点也没有改变吗?
How about your equipment? That hasn't changed either?

369
00:31:56,707 --> 00:31:59,293
A1的形状，一直都是。现在你应该记住这一点。
A1 shape, always was. Now you ought to remember that.

370
00:31:59,377 --> 00:32:01,480
我记得你需要一个新的锯筒。你有吗?
I remember you needing a new saw cylinder. You got one?

371
00:32:01,504 --> 00:32:05,174
好吧,我……我还没在市场上找到能和旧的一样好的。
Well, I... I can't find one on the market to equal the old one yet.

372
00:32:05,258 --> 00:32:06,777
来吧，来吧，和我一起喝杯咖啡。
Come on, come on, have some coffee with me.

373
00:32:06,801 --> 00:32:09,804
我们都准备好了。
We're all ready for you.

374
00:32:09,887 --> 00:32:16,811
我猜当你昨晚看到我的杜松子酒被烧成灰烬时，你一定想到明天早上你可能会得到一大笔生意。
I guess when you saw my gin burnin' down last night, you must have figured you might get a good deal of business thrown your way in the morning.

375
00:32:16,894 --> 00:32:19,105
你想知道吗?
You wanna know something?

376
00:32:19,188 --> 00:32:22,733
我总是很乐意知道一些事情当有事情需要知道的时候。
I'm always glad to know something when there's something to know.

377
00:32:22,817 --> 00:32:25,153
我昨晚没看到你的火。
I never did see that fire of yours last night.

378
00:32:25,236 --> 00:32:27,488
不，先生，不，先生。
No, sir. No, sir.

379
00:32:27,572 --> 00:32:30,241
来吧。来我家喝点咖啡吧。
Come on. Come on in my house and have some coffee.

380
00:32:30,324 --> 00:32:34,245
现在，你，你也来。来吧，来吧，伙计。
Now, you, you come too. Come on, come on, man.

381
00:32:34,328 --> 00:32:36,914
不，先生，我昨晚没看到你的火。
No, sir, I never did see that fire of yours last night.

382
00:32:36,998 --> 00:32:41,919
我们一吃完晚饭就上床睡觉了，直到早上吃早饭的时候我才知道你的轧棉机烧坏了。
We hit the sack right after supper and I didn't know until breakfast time this morning that your cotton gin burned down.

383
00:32:42,003 --> 00:32:43,337
哦，宝贝娃娃，出来。
Oh, Baby Doll, come out here.

384
00:32:43,421 --> 00:32:45,047
到这里来。过来，娃娃。
Come here. Come here, Baby Doll.

385
00:32:45,131 --> 00:32:48,634
我要你过来见见辛迪加种植园的瓦卡罗先生。
I want you to come right over here and meet Mr. Vacarro from the Syndicate Plantation.

386
00:32:48,718 --> 00:32:50,178
你叫什么名字，瓦卡罗?
Say, what's your first name, Vacarro?

387
00:32:50,261 --> 00:32:52,138
-席尔瓦。-怎么拼?
- Silva. - How do you spell it?

388
00:32:52,221 --> 00:32:54,348
资本S-I-L-V-A。
Capital S-I-L-V-A.

389
00:32:54,432 --> 00:32:56,767
果然吗?就像一线希望?
Sure enough? Like a silver linin'?

390
00:32:56,851 --> 00:32:59,854
嗯，黑暗中总有一线希望。
Well, every cloud has got a silver linin'.

391
00:32:59,937 --> 00:33:02,356
这是什么，《圣经》里的?
Oh, what's that from, the Bible?

392
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:04,275
不，是鹅妈妈的书。
No, the Mother Goose book.

393
00:33:06,527 --> 00:33:08,905
那个名字听起来很陌生。
That name sounds foreign.

394
00:33:08,988 --> 00:33:10,656
是的，梅根太太。
It is, Mrs. Meighan.

395
00:33:10,740 --> 00:33:14,035
我是那个经营辛迪加种植园的德国佬。
I'm known as the wop that runs the Syndicate Plantation.

396
00:33:14,118 --> 00:33:15,411
不要骂自己。
Don't call yourself names.

397
00:33:15,495 --> 00:33:17,497
让其他人骂你吧。
Let the other folks call you names.

398
00:33:17,580 --> 00:33:19,665
你真是个幸运的家伙，席尔瓦。
Well, you sure are a lucky fella, Silva.

399
00:33:19,749 --> 00:33:21,000
镀金甚至镀镍。
Gold or even nickel-plated.

400
00:33:21,083 --> 00:33:24,795
你真幸运，我现在能接你这种身材的活。
Oh, you sure are lucky that I could take a job on of your size right now.

401
00:33:24,879 --> 00:33:28,424
你看，你是我最近的邻居，我相信睦邻政策。
You see, you're my closest neighbor and I believe in the good neighbor policy.

402
00:33:28,508 --> 00:33:31,552
你帮了我一个忙我也帮了你一个忙，瓦卡罗先生。
You do me a good turn and I do you a good turn, Mr. Vacarro.

403
00:33:31,636 --> 00:33:34,889
以牙还牙是我们赖以生存的政策。
Tit for tat and tat for tit is the policy we live on.

404
00:33:34,972 --> 00:33:36,140
是的,先生。
Yes, sir.

405
00:33:36,224 --> 00:33:38,226
阿姨玫瑰。玫瑰阿姨安慰。
Aunt Rose. Aunt Rose Comfort.

406
00:33:38,309 --> 00:33:40,853
哦，宝贝娃娃。娃娃。
Oh, Baby Doll. Baby Doll.

407
00:33:40,937 --> 00:33:44,252
宝贝，让你爸爸的老处女姐姐给瓦卡罗先生端一壶新咖啡。
Baby, get your daddy's old maid sister to bring out a fresh pot of coffee for Mr. Vacarro.

408
00:33:44,315 --> 00:33:47,443
-自己去找她?——亲爱的。
- Get her yourself? - Honey.

409
00:33:47,527 --> 00:33:50,988
亲爱的，亲爱的，亲爱的。
Honey, honey, honey.

410
00:33:51,072 --> 00:33:54,200
现在我要你取悦这些先生们。
Now I want you to entertain these gentlemen.

411
00:33:54,283 --> 00:33:55,743
噢,看。看，看，看。
Oh, look. Look, look, look, look.

412
00:33:55,826 --> 00:33:57,662
哦，看她的脸红。看。
Oh, look at her blush. Look.

413
00:33:57,745 --> 00:34:00,456
看看她的脸红。哦，这是我的宝贝。
Look at her blush. Oh, this is my Baby.

414
00:34:00,540 --> 00:34:02,041
哦，这是我的小女儿。
Oh, this is my little girl.

415
00:34:02,124 --> 00:34:03,751
她的每一分珍贵都是我的。
Every precious ounce of her is mine.

416
00:34:03,834 --> 00:34:06,128
Bluh-bluh。Muah。
Bluh-bluh. Muah.

417
00:34:06,212 --> 00:34:08,381
阿姨玫瑰!玫瑰阿姨安慰!
Aunt Rose! Aunt Rose Comfort!

418
00:34:15,680 --> 00:34:19,850
请原谅我打哈欠。我们昨晚睡得很晚。
Excuse my yawn. We was up awful late last night.

419
00:34:24,981 --> 00:34:27,316
这么说你是德国人?
So you're a wop?

420
00:34:27,400 --> 00:34:29,110
不，我是西西里人，梅根太太。
No, I'm a Sicilian, Mrs. Meighan.

421
00:34:29,193 --> 00:34:31,445
一个非常古老的民族。
A very ancient people.

422
00:34:31,529 --> 00:34:35,616
——这一切。-不，姐姐。西西里。
- Shis. - No, Sis. Sicilian.

423
00:34:35,700 --> 00:34:38,244
我来自科珀斯克里斯蒂。
I'm from Corpus Christi.

424
00:34:38,327 --> 00:34:40,413
哦，真不寻常。
Oh, how unusual.

425
00:34:40,496 --> 00:34:45,793
亲爱的，中午，我要你带瓦卡罗先生去棉花王酒店吃鸡肉晚餐。
Honey, at noon, I want you to take Mr. Vacarro in town to the Cotton King Hotel for a chicken dinner.

426
00:34:45,876 --> 00:34:48,546
签上我的名字。
Sign my name.

427
00:34:48,629 --> 00:34:53,301
只有当你倒霉的时候，瓦卡罗先生，你才会发现谁是你的朋友我要证明这一点。
You know, it's only when bad luck hits you, Mr. Vacarro, that you find out who your friends are and I mean to prove it.

428
00:34:53,384 --> 00:34:56,673
宝贝娃娃，我要你在家里招待这位先生。
Baby Doll, I want you to entertain this gentleman in the house.

429
00:34:56,721 --> 00:34:58,055
这是睦邻政策。
It's a good neighbor policy.

430
00:34:58,139 --> 00:34:59,890
俗话说得好，以牙还牙。
Tit for tat and tat for tit as they say.

431
00:34:59,974 --> 00:35:04,145
你帮了我一个忙，我也帮了你一个忙，没错。
You do me a good turn and I do you a good turn some time in the future, that's right.

432
00:35:04,228 --> 00:35:06,230
来吧。来吧，宝贝娃娃。来吧。
Come on now. Come on, Baby Doll. Come on.

433
00:35:06,314 --> 00:35:10,276
现在让马车动起来。让他们动起来。
Now make those wagons move now. Get them rollin'.

434
00:35:10,359 --> 00:35:12,862
在那房子里谁都不舒服。
Can't make nobody comfortable in that house.

435
00:35:12,945 --> 00:35:15,531
比如你能不能找到一把椅子坐下。
Like if you can find a chair to sit down on.

436
00:35:17,867 --> 00:35:19,785
你要咖啡吗?
You want coffee?

437
00:35:19,869 --> 00:35:23,122
不，只是一杯凉水。谢谢你，女士。
No, just a cool drink of water. Thank you, ma'am.

438
00:35:23,205 --> 00:35:26,375
好吧，家里的水是暖的。
Oh, well, the house water runs warm.

439
00:35:26,459 --> 00:35:33,841
但如果你有精力使用那边的旧水泵，你可以从那个水箱里给自己弄到一杯清凉的饮料。
But if you got the energy to work that old pump over there, you can get yourself a nice cool drink from that there cistern.

440
00:35:33,924 --> 00:35:36,177
我有精力燃烧。
I got energy to burn.

441
00:35:51,776 --> 00:35:54,695
把他们的垃圾倒在院子里。
Dump their garbage in the yard.

442
00:35:54,779 --> 00:35:56,989
无知、放纵和恶臭。
Ignorance and indulgence and stink.

443
00:35:57,073 --> 00:35:59,283
我觉得年轻的梅根太太闻起来很香。
I thought that young Mrs. Meighan smelled pretty good.

444
00:35:59,367 --> 00:36:01,952
你把鼻子贴在棉花上。
You keep your nose to the cotton.

445
00:36:02,036 --> 00:36:04,997
水有时来，有时不来。
Sometimes water comes, sometimes it don't.

446
00:36:05,081 --> 00:36:07,375
好吧，这次会的。
Well, this time it will.

447
00:36:10,961 --> 00:36:14,298
请给我一杯清凉可口的井水。
Bring me a drink of that nice cool well water, please.

448
00:36:15,966 --> 00:36:18,094
“这么说你是德国人?”
"So you're a wop?"

449
00:36:21,931 --> 00:36:27,228
我的手臂已经没有力气从井里打水了。
I don't have the strength anymore in my arm that I used to to draw water out of that well.

450
00:36:27,311 --> 00:36:29,063
你想喝杯凉水吗?
Would you like a cool drink of water?

451
00:36:29,146 --> 00:36:32,358
你好!我是Rose Comfort McCorkle阿姨。
How do you do? I'm Aunt Rose Comfort McCorkle.

452
00:36:32,441 --> 00:36:37,571
我哥哥是宝贝娃娃的爸爸，tc·卡森·麦科克尔先生。
My brother was Baby Doll's daddy, Mr. T.C. Carson McCorkle.

453
00:36:37,655 --> 00:36:45,329
我一直来这里，自从…嗯，我现在想不起来是什么时候。
I've been visiting here since, uh... Well, just now I can't remember just when it was since.

454
00:36:45,413 --> 00:36:48,040
我希望你不介意用葫芦喝水。
I hope you don't mind drinking out of a gourd.

455
00:36:48,124 --> 00:36:50,459
哦。谢谢你！
Oh. Thank you.

456
00:36:54,588 --> 00:36:59,802
打扰一下。那只老母鸡弗斯又回到我厨房了。
Excuse me, please. That old hen Fuss has got back in my kitchen again.

457
00:37:01,637 --> 00:37:06,058
我还能想出更糟的办法来打发一下午给梅根太太送清凉的井水呢。
Why, I could think of worse ways to spend an afternoon delivering cool well water to Mrs. Meighan.

458
00:37:13,733 --> 00:37:15,943
你守着棉花，听到了吗?
You stay with the cotton, you hear?

459
00:37:16,026 --> 00:37:18,154
继续，继续用棉花。
Go on, stay with the cotton.

460
00:37:23,951 --> 00:37:26,245
在水中有这样的区别。
There's such a difference in water.

461
00:37:26,328 --> 00:37:28,706
你可能不这么认为，但确实有。
You wouldn't think so, but there certainly is.

462
00:37:30,624 --> 00:37:34,170
我猜你在这里住的时间不长，梅根太太。
I take it you've not had this place long, Mrs. Meighan.

463
00:37:34,253 --> 00:37:36,338
不，我们的时间不长。
No, we ain't had it long.

464
00:37:38,549 --> 00:37:41,761
虎尾路没有收垃圾的人吗?
Don't you have garbage collectors on Tiger Tail Road?

465
00:37:43,345 --> 00:37:52,438
哦，好吧，好吧，他们来这里要多花点钱，而阿奇·李……哦，我不知道。有时我几乎要放弃了。
Oh, well, well, it costs a little bit extra for them to come out here and Archie Lee... Oh, I don't know. I almost give up sometimes.

466
00:37:55,316 --> 00:38:00,196
你是说这房子里有一堆没有家具的房间吗?
Did I understand you to say you've got a bunch of unfurnished rooms in this house?

467
00:38:00,279 --> 00:38:05,576
五套完整的家具被理想的随走随付家具公司运走。
Five complete sets of furniture hauled away by the Ideal Pay As You Go Plan Furniture Company.

468
00:38:07,578 --> 00:38:09,955
你什么时候遭遇这种不幸的?
When did this misfortune fall upon you?

469
00:38:11,582 --> 00:38:13,375
昨天。
Yesterday.

470
00:38:13,459 --> 00:38:15,836
那不是很可怕吗?昨天。
Ain't that awful? Yesterday.

471
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:19,048
我们俩在同一天遭遇了不幸。
Both of us had misfortunes on the same day.

472
00:38:19,131 --> 00:38:20,567
——嗯?-你的家具丢了。
- Hmm? - You lost your furniture.

473
00:38:20,591 --> 00:38:24,136
-我的轧棉机烧了。-是啊。
- My cotton gin burned down. - Oh, yeah.

474
00:38:24,220 --> 00:38:26,764
-太巧了。-那是什么?
- Quite a coincidence. - What's that?

475
00:38:26,847 --> 00:38:29,850
我说这是不幸的巧合。
I said it was a coincidence of misfortune.

476
00:38:29,934 --> 00:38:31,852
哦，当然。
Oh, well, sure.

477
00:38:31,936 --> 00:38:34,897
我是说，一堆没有家具的房间你能做什么?
I mean, what can you do with a bunch of unfurnished rooms?

478
00:38:38,234 --> 00:38:42,238
我们可以玩捉迷藏。
Well, we could play hide and seek.

479
00:38:42,321 --> 00:38:45,449
不是我。我不擅长运动。
Not me. I'm not athletic.

480
00:38:45,533 --> 00:38:52,623
是啊，当我来到这个县接手辛迪加种植园的管理时，这房子是空的。
Yeah, well, when I arrived in this county to take over the management of the Syndicate Plantation, this house was empty.

481
00:38:52,706 --> 00:38:55,835
-我听说那里闹鬼。-是啊，那里闹鬼
- I was told it was haunted. - Oh, yeah, it was haunted.

482
00:38:55,918 --> 00:38:59,046
这就是为什么阿奇·李几乎不花一分钱就得到了它。
That's why Archie Lee got it for almost nothin'.

483
00:38:59,129 --> 00:39:02,174
有时我不知道该去哪里，该做什么。
Sometimes I don't know where to go or what to do.

484
00:39:02,258 --> 00:39:03,843
嗯，这并不罕见。
Well, that's not uncommon.

485
00:39:03,926 --> 00:39:05,886
人们没有受过教育就来到这个世界。
People enter this world without instruction.

486
00:39:05,970 --> 00:39:10,891
——嗯?-我说…这是你的早餐吗，梅根太太?
- Hmm? - I said... Is that your breakfast, Mrs. Meighan?

487
00:39:13,602 --> 00:39:18,482
我说，人们来到这个世界上，没有人告诉他们该去哪里，该做什么。
I said people come into this world without instruction of where to go or what to do.

488
00:39:18,566 --> 00:39:22,027
所以他们徘徊了一会儿，然后就走了。
So they wander a little and then go away.

489
00:39:22,111 --> 00:39:25,239
漂移一会儿，然后消失。
Drift for a while and then vanish.

490
00:39:25,322 --> 00:39:28,951
所以要为新人腾出空间。
And so make room for newcomers.

491
00:39:29,034 --> 00:39:32,997
Old-goers,新人。
Old-goers, newcomers.

492
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:35,291
来来回回。
Going and coming, back and forth.

493
00:39:35,374 --> 00:39:37,960
冲,冲。
Rush, rush.

494
00:39:38,043 --> 00:39:40,671
永久的,什么都没有。
Permanent, nothing.

495
00:39:43,340 --> 00:39:48,220
什么生活……持续的时间足以让你认真对待它……
Anything living... that lasts long enough to take it serious...

496
00:39:50,514 --> 00:39:52,308
这是什么?
What's this?

497
00:39:52,391 --> 00:39:59,189
这是那辆旧的皮尔斯-阿罗汽车，是多宾太太的，她曾经是这栋房子的主人，现在还在这里出没。
This is that old Pierce-Arrow car, belong to Mrs. Dobine, the lady that used to own this house and haunts it now.

498
00:39:59,273 --> 00:40:00,691
去哪里，夫人?
Where to, madam?

499
00:40:00,774 --> 00:40:02,985
哦，我们要扮演司机。
Oh, we're gonna play chauffeur.

500
00:40:05,738 --> 00:40:08,449
好的，再见。
Yeah, goodbye now.

501
00:40:08,532 --> 00:40:14,580
开车带我去河边开着所有的窗户让我凉快点。
Hey, drive me along the river with all the windows open to cool me off.

502
00:40:14,663 --> 00:40:16,103
司机坐在前座。
The chauffeur sits in the front seat.

503
00:40:16,165 --> 00:40:17,791
前座没有靠垫。
The front seat's got no cushion.

504
00:40:17,875 --> 00:40:19,251
哦,是的。
Oh, yeah.

505
00:40:19,335 --> 00:40:22,838
来吧，伙计们!站起来，我们走!
Come on, men! Get on your big feet, let's go!

506
00:40:22,922 --> 00:40:26,300
-来吧!-哦，我们来轧棉花吧。
- Come on! - Oh, let's gin some cotton.

507
00:40:26,383 --> 00:40:29,053
-小心，伙计们!-站起来。
- Look out, men! - Get on those big feet.

508
00:40:29,136 --> 00:40:31,055
我们进去吧。
Let's get in here.

509
00:40:31,138 --> 00:40:33,307
哦，让我们剪一些棉花吧。
Oh, let's cut some cotton.

510
00:40:36,018 --> 00:40:43,567
自从理想的随走随付计划家具公司失去耐心后，很难找到一个舒适的地方坐下……当理想出现时，你很难舒服地坐着
It's hard to find a place to sit since the Ideal Pay As You Go Plan Furniture Company lost patience, to sit in comfort... It's hard to sit in comfort when the Ideal

511
00:40:43,651 --> 00:40:49,406
现付现付的人会失去耐心……你的杜松子酒烧尽了。
Pay As You Go Plan people lose their patience... and your gin burns down.

512
00:40:57,247 --> 00:41:00,417
-你能把腿挪一下吗?-但这里很凉快。
- Would you move your leg? - But it's cool here.

513
00:41:00,501 --> 00:41:03,462
坐起来很舒服。
Comfortable to sit in.

514
00:41:03,545 --> 00:41:07,091
-这是什么?-那是我的魅力手镯。
- What's this here? - That's my charm bracelet.

515
00:41:07,174 --> 00:41:09,843
我爸爸给我的。
My daddy gave it to me.

516
00:41:09,927 --> 00:41:12,137
这就是十诫。
Them's the Ten Commandments.

517
00:41:12,221 --> 00:41:14,556
-这些呢?-我的生日。
- And these here? - My birthdays.

518
00:41:16,308 --> 00:41:18,686
你过了多少个迷人的生日?
How many charming birthdays have you had?

519
00:41:18,769 --> 00:41:23,148
手镯上有多少魅力就有多少。
As many as there are charms on the bracelet.

520
00:41:23,232 --> 00:41:26,485
-你介意我…-数一数。
- Do you mind if I... - Count them.

521
00:41:32,741 --> 00:41:37,746
十五，十六，十七，十八，十九。
Fifteen, sixteen, seventeen, eighteen, nineteen.

522
00:41:37,830 --> 00:41:39,873
这是所有。
That's all.

523
00:41:39,957 --> 00:41:41,834
明天我就20岁了。
I'll be 20 tomorrow.

524
00:41:41,917 --> 00:41:50,759
明天是选举日，也是我的生日，也是富兰克林·德拉诺·罗斯福先生第一次当选的日子。
Tomorrow is election day and my birthday and the day that Mr. Franklin Delano Roosevelt was elected for his first term.

525
00:41:50,843 --> 00:41:55,097
这对国家来说是伟大的一天，原因有二。
It's a great day for the country for both reasons.

526
00:41:55,180 --> 00:41:58,225
他是个值得尊敬的人。
Oh, he was a man to respect.

527
00:41:58,308 --> 00:42:01,603
你是位值得尊敬的女士，梅根太太。
Well, you're a lady to respect, Mrs. Meighan.

528
00:42:01,687 --> 00:42:04,231
我吗?不。
Me? No.

529
00:42:04,314 --> 00:42:07,026
我连四年级都没读完。
I never got past the fourth grade.

530
00:42:07,109 --> 00:42:09,194
你为什么辞职?
Why'd you quit?

531
00:42:09,278 --> 00:42:13,407
我在长除法上遇到了很多麻烦。
Well, I had a great deal of trouble with long division.

532
00:42:13,490 --> 00:42:14,950
是吗?
Yeah?

533
00:42:15,034 --> 00:42:27,921
老师会让我到黑板前做长除法的一道题，我就会走到黑板前，把头靠在黑板上，哭啊哭啊哭。
The teacher would send me up to the blackboard to work on a problem in long division and I would go up to the blackboard, lean my head against it and just cry and cry and cry.

534
00:42:30,924 --> 00:42:32,968
你能把腿挪一下吗?
Would you move your leg?

535
00:42:34,720 --> 00:42:37,514
你想移动我的腿吗?
Do you wanna move my leg?

536
00:42:37,598 --> 00:42:41,143
是啊，否则我出不去。
Yeah, otherwise I can't get out.

537
00:42:41,226 --> 00:42:43,854
好的。
Okay.

538
00:42:43,937 --> 00:42:50,360
嗯…我就一直哭啊哭啊。
Well... I would just cry and cry and cry.

539
00:42:50,444 --> 00:42:57,117
最后，我离开了学校……哦，一个没有受过教育的女孩就是一个没有教育的女孩…
Well, finally, I left school and... Oh, a girl without education is a girl without edu...

540
00:42:59,369 --> 00:43:02,247
Vacarro先生吗?
Mr. Vacarro?

541
00:43:02,331 --> 00:43:04,500
我只是来买些山核桃。
Just picking up a few pecan nuts.

542
00:43:06,543 --> 00:43:08,962
哦，不好意思。
Oh, excuse me.

543
00:43:09,046 --> 00:43:15,344
不好意思，瓦卡罗先生，我可不想吃一个人在嘴里咬碎的坚果。
Excuse me, Mr. Vacarro, but I wouldn't dream of eating a nut which a man had cracked in his mouth.

544
00:43:15,427 --> 00:43:18,597
你有很多优点。
You've got many refinements.

545
00:43:18,680 --> 00:43:21,183
谢谢你！
Thank you.

546
00:43:21,266 --> 00:43:26,730
现在我觉得你不用担心长除法的失败了。
Now I don't think you need worry about your failure at long division.

547
00:43:26,814 --> 00:43:29,441
毕竟，你通过了短除法。
After all, you got through short division.

548
00:43:29,525 --> 00:43:32,653
短间隔是所有女士都该应付的。
Short division's all a lady ought to be called on to cope with.

549
00:43:32,736 --> 00:43:35,072
是的。
Yeah.

550
00:43:35,155 --> 00:43:39,409
我现在该进去了。
Well, I ought to be going in now.

551
00:43:39,493 --> 00:43:41,078
哦。
Oh.

552
00:43:44,748 --> 00:43:49,920
但每次看到那么多空房间，我都很沮丧。
But I get so depressed going through all them empty rooms.

553
00:43:50,003 --> 00:43:51,880
所有的房间都是空的吗?
All the rooms empty?

554
00:43:51,964 --> 00:43:53,841
除了育儿室和厨房。
All except for the nursery and the kitchen.

555
00:43:53,924 --> 00:43:56,218
房间里的东西都是花钱买的。
The stuff in them rooms is paid for.

556
00:43:56,301 --> 00:43:58,720
你有个孩子在托儿所吗?
You have a child in the nursery?

557
00:43:58,804 --> 00:44:01,640
我吗?不。
Me? No.

558
00:44:01,723 --> 00:44:04,184
我自己也睡在育儿室。
I sleep in the nursery myself.

559
00:44:04,268 --> 00:44:06,979
我把板条放在婴儿床上。
I let the slats down on the crib.

560
00:44:07,062 --> 00:44:09,148
你为什么睡在育儿室?
Why do you sleep in the nursery?

561
00:44:11,024 --> 00:44:14,361
瓦卡罗先生，这是个私人问题。
Mr. Vacarro, that's a personal question.

562
00:44:19,241 --> 00:44:23,162
我现在该进去了。
Well, I ought to be going in now.

563
00:44:34,256 --> 00:44:38,302
但你知道，那房子里有些房间我从没去过。
But you know, there are rooms in that house that I never been in.

564
00:44:38,385 --> 00:44:41,430
比如，阁楼。
Like, for instance, the attic.

565
00:44:41,513 --> 00:44:45,475
你知道大多数时候我都不敢一个人进那栋房子。
You know that most of the time I'm scared to go in that house by myself.

566
00:44:45,559 --> 00:44:48,270
就像昨晚火灾发生的时候。
You take like last night when the fire broke out.

567
00:44:48,353 --> 00:44:54,818
我在这里坐了好几个小时，好几个小时，好几个小时，等着阿奇·李回家，因为我害怕自己一个人进屋。
I sat here for hours and hours and hours waiting for Archie Lee to come home because I was scared of going in the house by myself.

568
00:44:54,902 --> 00:44:59,031
没有你丈夫的照顾，你一定很害怕。
Well, it must have been scary without your husband to look out for you.

569
00:44:59,114 --> 00:45:01,116
哦，我告诉你。
Oh, I'm telling you.

570
00:45:01,200 --> 00:45:06,580
大火爆发了，整个天空都被疯狂的影子照亮了。
The fire broke out and lit up the whole sky with crazy shadows.

571
00:45:06,663 --> 00:45:08,999
我们家里也没有可乐。
And we didn't have a Coke in the house.

572
00:45:09,082 --> 00:45:10,876
我在生阿奇·李的气。
Oh, I was mad at Archie Lee.

573
00:45:10,959 --> 00:45:13,253
你生梅根先生的气。关于什么?
You were mad at Mr. Meighan. What about?

574
00:45:13,337 --> 00:45:16,131
他走了，把我留在屋里，可乐也没喝。
He went off and left me without a Coke in the house.

575
00:45:16,215 --> 00:45:18,050
离开了…没有可乐，是吗?
Went off and left... Without a Coke, did he?

576
00:45:18,133 --> 00:45:20,469
是的，他说了。当然了。
Yes, he did. He certainly did.

577
00:45:20,552 --> 00:45:24,223
直到火灾发生很久之后他才回来。
And he didn't get back until way after the fire had broken out.

578
00:45:24,306 --> 00:45:30,812
我的眼睛里，鼻子里，喉咙里都是烟。哦。
And I had got smoke in my eyes, in my nose, in my throat. Ooh.

579
00:45:30,896 --> 00:45:35,317
噢，我当时太紧张了，我哭了。
Oh, I was in such a worn out nervous condition, I cried.

580
00:45:35,400 --> 00:45:39,905
最后，我吃了两茶匙止痛药。
Finally, I took two teaspoons of paregoric.

581
00:45:39,988 --> 00:45:42,407
听起来你昨晚过得很不舒服。
Sounds like you passed a very uncomfortable night.

582
00:45:42,491 --> 00:45:45,077
哦，听起来怎么样?
Oh, sounds like?

583
00:45:45,160 --> 00:45:47,371
哦，是的。
Ooh, it was.

584
00:45:49,790 --> 00:45:52,292
你说梅根先生晚饭后就不见了。
So Mr. Meighan, you say, disappeared after supper.

585
00:45:53,627 --> 00:45:55,003
嗯?
Huh?

586
00:45:55,087 --> 00:45:59,883
你说梅根先生晚饭后离开了一段时间?
You say Mr. Meighan left the house for a while after supper?

587
00:45:59,967 --> 00:46:02,010
哦，是的，有一会儿。
Oh, yeah, for a moment.

588
00:46:02,094 --> 00:46:04,972
就一会儿，嗯?
Just for a moment, huh?

589
00:46:05,055 --> 00:46:07,307
一分钟有多长?
How long a moment?

590
00:46:07,391 --> 00:46:08,850
你想说什么，瓦卡罗先生?
What are you driving at, Mr. Vacarro?

591
00:46:08,934 --> 00:46:10,560
开车吗?
Driving at?

592
00:46:10,644 --> 00:46:13,146
是的，你看我的眼神很好笑。
Yes, you're looking at me so funny.

593
00:46:13,230 --> 00:46:16,984
你还记得他消失了多久吗，梅根太太?
How long a moment did he disappear for, can you remember, Mrs. Meighan?

594
00:46:17,067 --> 00:46:18,360
哦，这有什么区别?
Oh, what difference does it make?

595
00:46:18,443 --> 00:46:22,614
我是说，这跟你有什么关系…你为什么要介意我问呢?
I mean, what does it matter to you... Why should you mind my asking?

596
00:46:22,698 --> 00:46:24,658
你说得好像我在受审似的。
You make it sound like I'm on trial for somethin'.

597
00:46:24,741 --> 00:46:27,077
你不喜欢假装自己是目击证人吗?
Don't you like to pretend like you're a witness?

598
00:46:29,371 --> 00:46:30,872
什么证人，瓦卡罗先生?
Witness of what, Mr. Vacarro?

599
00:46:30,956 --> 00:46:33,500
比如说，一起纵火案。
Oh, say, for instance, a case of arson.

600
00:46:35,752 --> 00:46:37,129
纵火是什么?
What's arson?

601
00:46:37,212 --> 00:46:40,215
故意放火毁坏财产。
The willful destruction of property by fire.

602
00:46:40,299 --> 00:46:42,467
——哦。——什么?
- Oh. - What?

603
00:46:42,551 --> 00:46:46,388
嗯,关于…我丈夫晚饭后离开，我可以解释
Well, about... about my husband leavin' after supper, I can explain that.

604
00:46:46,471 --> 00:46:48,223
-你能吗?-当然可以。
- Can you? - Oh, sure, I can.

605
00:46:48,307 --> 00:46:50,559
嗯,很好。现在你怎么解释呢?
Well, good. Now how can you explain it?

606
00:46:52,894 --> 00:46:56,398
怎么了，梅根太太?你不能集中思想吗?
What's the matter, Mrs. Meighan? Can't you collect your thoughts?

607
00:46:59,318 --> 00:47:02,070
你脑子里一片空白，对吧?
Your mind's a blank on the subject, hmm?

608
00:47:03,989 --> 00:47:10,078
你不记得你丈夫晚饭后为什么失踪了吗?
You find it impossible to remember just what your husband disappeared for after supper?

609
00:47:10,162 --> 00:47:14,458
你无法想象他去做了什么差事，对吧?你能吗?
You can't imagine what kind of errand he went on, can you? Can you?

610
00:47:14,541 --> 00:47:21,798
但当他回来的时候，嗯，让我想想，辛迪加种植园刚刚发生火灾。
But when he returned, well, let's see, the fire had just broken out at the Syndicate Plantation.

611
00:47:23,759 --> 00:47:26,696
瓦卡罗先生，我不知道你想说什么。
Mr. Vacarro, I can't imagine what you could possibly be drivin' at.

612
00:47:26,720 --> 00:47:28,555
没有?
No?

613
00:47:28,638 --> 00:47:31,308
你是个很不称职的证人，梅根夫人。
You're a very unsatisfactory witness, Mrs. Meighan.

614
00:47:34,895 --> 00:47:37,606
好吧，我们该别提这个话题了吗?
Well, should we drop the subject?

615
00:47:37,689 --> 00:47:40,525
-哦，我真希望你能来。-当然。
- Oh, I sure do wish you would. - Well, sure.

616
00:47:42,944 --> 00:47:45,572
为烧坏的杜松子酒哭也没用。
There's no use crying over a burned down gin.

617
00:47:49,076 --> 00:47:55,624
而且，就像你丈夫说的，这个世界是建立在以牙还牙的基础上的。
Besides, like your husband says, this world is built on the principle of tit for tat.

618
00:47:58,043 --> 00:48:00,212
你这话是什么意思?
What do you mean by that?

619
00:48:03,507 --> 00:48:05,342
没有任何明确的承诺。
Nothing specific.

620
00:48:08,720 --> 00:48:11,223
-你介意我…——什么?
- Do you mind if I... - What?

621
00:48:11,306 --> 00:48:13,225
坐下来?
Sit down?

622
00:48:13,308 --> 00:48:15,102
它足够坚固，能支撑我们俩吗?
Is it strong enough to support us both?

623
00:48:15,185 --> 00:48:17,979
嗯，我希望如此。
Well, I hope.

624
00:48:18,063 --> 00:48:20,941
现在让我们摇摆一下，好吗?
Now let's swing a little, huh?

625
00:48:21,024 --> 00:48:24,236
你看起来很紧张。
You seem all tense.

626
00:48:24,319 --> 00:48:27,280
运动使人放松。
Motion relaxes people.

627
00:48:27,364 --> 00:48:29,366
它就像一个摇篮。
It's like a cradle.

628
00:48:29,449 --> 00:48:31,535
摇篮使婴儿放松。
A cradle relaxes a baby.

629
00:48:33,870 --> 00:48:35,455
他们叫你宝贝，不是吗?
They call you Baby, don't they?

630
00:48:35,539 --> 00:48:37,082
哦，那是一种昵称。
Oh, that's sort of a nickname.

631
00:48:37,165 --> 00:48:40,627
在秋千上，你可以像在摇篮里一样放松。
Well, in a swing, you can relax just like in a cradle.

632
00:48:40,710 --> 00:48:42,796
好吧,我……我不喜欢荡秋千。这让我很震惊。
Well, I... I don't like to swing. It shakes me up.

633
00:48:42,879 --> 00:48:45,048
而且，我已经足够放松了。
Besides, I'm relaxed enough as much as necessary.

634
00:48:45,132 --> 00:48:46,466
哦，不，你不是。
Oh, no, you're not.

635
00:48:46,550 --> 00:48:48,301
你神经太紧张了吧?
Your nerves are all tied up, hmm?

636
00:48:48,385 --> 00:48:51,221
-你让我很紧张。-只是和你一起摇摆?
- Well, you make me nervous. - Just swinging with you?

637
00:48:51,304 --> 00:48:53,390
-不，不只是这样。-还有什么?
- No, not just that. - What else then?

638
00:48:53,473 --> 00:48:55,892
你问我的那些关于火灾的问题。
All them questions you asked me about the fire.

639
00:48:57,894 --> 00:49:01,523
我只是想问问你丈夫的情况。
I was only enquiring about your husband.

640
00:49:01,606 --> 00:49:04,192
关于他晚饭后离开家的事。
About his leaving the house after supper.

641
00:49:04,276 --> 00:49:08,238
但我没必要向你解释这些事。
But there's no reason why I should have to explain things to you.

642
00:49:08,321 --> 00:49:10,449
不。
No.

643
00:49:10,532 --> 00:49:12,659
我们应该放松吗?
Should we just relax?

644
00:49:17,914 --> 00:49:20,250
你能挪过去一点，腾出点地方来吗?
Would you move over and make a little room?

645
00:49:22,836 --> 00:49:24,629
那地方够你住吗?
Is that enough room for you?

646
00:49:24,713 --> 00:49:26,965
对我来说足够了。你呢?
It's enough for me. How about you?

647
00:49:30,218 --> 00:49:33,847
你丈夫说得很好。
It was a lovely remark your husband made.

648
00:49:33,930 --> 00:49:36,141
我是说睦邻政策。
The good neighbor policy, I mean.

649
00:49:38,059 --> 00:49:41,438
“你帮我一个忙，我也帮你一个忙。”
"You do me a good turn and I do you one."

650
00:49:44,024 --> 00:49:46,234
他是这么说的。
That was the way he put it.

651
00:49:53,950 --> 00:49:56,578
-好了。——谢谢。
- There now. - Thanks.

652
00:49:56,661 --> 00:50:00,165
有很多细小的棉绒漂浮在空气中。
There's a lot of fine cotton lint floating around in the air.

653
00:50:00,248 --> 00:50:03,210
我知道有。我鼻窦不舒服。
I know there is. It bothers my sinus.

654
00:50:03,293 --> 00:50:05,921
你是个很精致的女人，梅根太太。
Well, you're a very delicate woman, Mrs. Meighan.

655
00:50:07,881 --> 00:50:10,926
精致的?我吗?
Delicate? Me?

656
00:50:11,009 --> 00:50:14,846
你的东西不多，但还有选择。
There isn't much of you, but what there is is choice.

657
00:50:16,389 --> 00:50:18,642
-我可以说很美味。——嗯?
- Delectable, I might say. - Hmm?

658
00:50:20,185 --> 00:50:27,317
你fine-fibered…软……和光滑。
You're fine-fibered... soft... and smooth.

659
00:50:29,361 --> 00:50:33,490
瓦卡罗先生，我们的谈话转向个人了。
Mr. Vacarro, our conversation certainly is taking a personal turn.

660
00:50:33,573 --> 00:50:35,534
你让我想起了棉花。
You make me think of cotton.

661
00:50:35,617 --> 00:50:38,119
不。
No.

662
00:50:38,203 --> 00:50:54,427
没有织物或布料，甚至没有绸缎或丝绸……没有哪种纤维，甚至连棉纤维都没有……拥有绝对细腻的肌肤。
No fabric or cloth, not even satin or silk cloth... and no kind of fiber, not even a cotton fiber... has the absolute delicacy of your skin.

663
00:50:54,511 --> 00:50:57,430
我该怎么说呢?谢谢还是什么?
Well, what should I say? Thanks or something?

664
00:50:57,514 --> 00:51:00,016
不，你笑就行了，梅根太太。
No, you just smile, Mrs. Meighan.

665
00:51:00,100 --> 00:51:03,645
你的笑容很迷人。
You've got an attractive smile.

666
00:51:03,728 --> 00:51:04,938
——酒窝。——没有。
- Dimples. - No.

667
00:51:05,021 --> 00:51:06,940
哦，不，你需要。
Oh, yes, you do.

668
00:51:07,023 --> 00:51:08,817
来吧，笑一笑，梅根太太。
Come on now, smile, Mrs. Meighan.

669
00:51:08,900 --> 00:51:11,820
你看，你有，你有。
There, you see, you do, you do have them.

670
00:51:11,903 --> 00:51:14,197
别碰我。请不要碰我。
Don't touch me. Please don't touch me.

671
00:51:14,281 --> 00:51:17,075
-我不喜欢被碰。-那你傻笑什么?
- I don't like to be touched. - Well, why do you giggle?

672
00:51:17,158 --> 00:51:21,121
因为你让我觉得有点歇斯底里，瓦卡罗先生。
Because you make me feel kind of hysterical, Mr. Vacarro.

673
00:51:21,204 --> 00:51:23,873
-真的吗?-瓦卡罗先生。
- I do? - Mr. Vacarro.

674
00:51:23,957 --> 00:51:25,542
是吗?
Yes?

675
00:51:28,003 --> 00:51:30,505
我…我去弄点柠檬水。
I... I think I'll go and make us some lemonade.

676
00:51:32,757 --> 00:51:35,176
你为什么要那样做?
What did you do that for?

677
00:51:35,260 --> 00:51:38,138
我不想被剥夺和你在一起的快乐。
I don't wanna be deprived of the pleasure of your company.

678
00:51:39,639 --> 00:51:42,475
还没有。
Not yet.

679
00:51:42,559 --> 00:51:45,854
瓦卡罗先生，你真是越来越熟了。
Oh, Mr. Vacarro, you certainly are getting familiar.

680
00:51:45,937 --> 00:51:48,231
难道你没有一点爱玩的精神吗?
Don't you have any fun-loving spirit about you?

681
00:51:48,315 --> 00:51:50,233
这可不好玩。
Well, this isn't fun.

682
00:51:50,317 --> 00:51:52,986
那你还傻笑什么?
Well, why do you giggle then, hmm?

683
00:51:53,069 --> 00:51:55,322
-因为我怕痒。-你怕痒?
- Because I'm ticklish. - You're ticklish?

684
00:51:57,449 --> 00:51:59,909
别那么神经质。
Don't be so skittish.

685
00:51:59,993 --> 00:52:02,662
一个……好吧，那我就起来。
A... alright, I'll get up then.

686
00:52:06,833 --> 00:52:08,293
继续。
Go on.

687
00:52:14,466 --> 00:52:17,052
哦。
Oh.

688
00:52:17,135 --> 00:52:19,179
我觉得很虚弱。
I feel so weak.

689
00:52:29,814 --> 00:52:33,943
哦，我的头很模糊。
Oh, my head is fuzzy.

690
00:52:36,404 --> 00:52:38,156
——模糊?——嗯。
- Fuzzy? - Hmm.

691
00:52:40,408 --> 00:52:43,078
毛茸茸的，嗡嗡作响的。
Fuzzy and buzzy.

692
00:52:49,084 --> 00:52:51,461
我的头在晃荡。
My head is swinging round.

693
00:52:56,591 --> 00:52:59,177
肯定是甩得太厉害了。
Must have been that swinging that done it.

694
00:53:22,409 --> 00:53:24,411
-我胳膊上有东西吗?——没有。
- Is there something on my arm? - No.

695
00:53:24,494 --> 00:53:29,290
哦,然后…-别说了，感觉很好笑。-感觉如何?
Oh, then... - Cut it out, it feels funny. - How does it feel?

696
00:53:29,374 --> 00:53:32,252
上上下下都觉得很好笑。
Oh, it feels funny all up and down.

697
00:53:32,335 --> 00:53:33,461
别换我了，好吗?
Quit switchin' me, will you?

698
00:53:33,545 --> 00:53:34,730
我只是把苍蝇赶走。
I'm just shooing the flies off.

699
00:53:34,754 --> 00:53:37,882
哦，好吧，他们不会伤害什么。
Oh, well, they don't hurt nothin'.

700
00:53:37,966 --> 00:53:40,093
别闹了，不然我要打电话了。
Now cut it out or I'm gonna call.

701
00:53:40,176 --> 00:53:41,803
给谁打电话?
Well, call who?

702
00:53:41,886 --> 00:53:44,431
路上的男孩。
Boy on the road.

703
00:53:44,514 --> 00:53:47,225
好吧，那就打电话吧。
Well, go on, call then.

704
00:53:47,308 --> 00:53:49,936
男孩!
Boy!

705
00:53:51,646 --> 00:53:53,898
你就不能大声点吗?
Can't you call any louder, hmm?

706
00:53:53,982 --> 00:53:55,817
-我觉得…-你就不能大声点吗?
- I feel so... - Can't you call any louder?

707
00:53:55,900 --> 00:54:01,448
我…我觉得很好笑。是什么……-我怎么了?-你只是在放松。
I... I feel so funny. What's... - What's the matter with me? - You're just relaxing.

708
00:54:01,531 --> 00:54:03,450
屈服现在别再反抗了。
Give in. Now stop fighting it.

709
00:54:03,533 --> 00:54:14,961
哦，我不是…我不是在反抗，但是…是你和你对…关于我…我的丈夫…怀疑吗?怀疑如?
Oh, I'm not... I'm not fighting it, but it's... it's you and your suspicions about... about my... my husband... Suspicions? Suspicions such as?

710
00:54:15,044 --> 00:54:17,672
-他烧了你的杜松子酒——好吗?
- That he burned down your gin. - Well?

711
00:54:17,756 --> 00:54:20,258
-他没有。-是吗?
- Well, he didn't. - Didn't he?

712
00:54:20,341 --> 00:54:23,136
不，他没有。
No, he didn't.

713
00:54:23,219 --> 00:54:26,014
他……他……他没有。
He... he... he didn't.

714
00:54:26,097 --> 00:54:28,933
我现在要进屋去。
I'm going in the house now.

715
00:54:29,017 --> 00:54:31,728
你相信有鬼吗，梅根太太?
You believe in ghosts, Mrs. Meighan?

716
00:54:31,811 --> 00:54:33,480
我做的事。
I do.

717
00:54:33,563 --> 00:54:36,149
我相信恶灵的存在。
I believe in the presence of evil spirits.

718
00:54:36,232 --> 00:54:38,985
你说的是什么邪灵?
What evil spirits you talking about?

719
00:54:39,068 --> 00:54:47,911
暴力和狡猾的灵魂，恶毒，残忍，背叛，破坏。
Spirits of violence and cunning, malevolence, cruelty, treachery, destruction.

720
00:54:47,994 --> 00:54:50,997
这只是人类的特征。
Them's just human characteristics.

721
00:54:51,080 --> 00:55:02,842
恶灵出没于人心，占据人心，从一个人的心蔓延到另一个人的心，就像火焰从一片叶子蔓延到另一片叶子
The evil spirits that haunt the human heart and take possession of it and spread from one human heart to another human heart, the way a fire goes springing from leaf to leaf

722
00:55:02,926 --> 00:55:07,472
一根树枝接一根树枝，直到整个森林都被它点燃。
and branch to branch in a tree till the forest is all aflame with it.

723
00:55:07,555 --> 00:55:09,724
你只是脑子着火了。
You just got fire on the brain.

724
00:55:09,808 --> 00:55:12,936
我认为它比表面上看起来的要多。
I see it as more than it seems to be on the surface.

725
00:55:13,019 --> 00:55:16,773
我昨晚看到了那些恶灵的爆炸。
I saw it last night as an explosion of those evil spirits.

726
00:55:16,856 --> 00:55:23,571
我和它搏斗，我冲进去，打它，踩它，对着它喊着上帝的诅咒。
I fought it, I ran into it, beating it and stamping it, shouting a curse of God at it.

727
00:55:23,655 --> 00:55:25,865
他们把我拖了出来，我快要窒息了。
They dragged me out, suffocating.

728
00:55:25,949 --> 00:55:28,034
我被打败了。
I was defeated.

729
00:55:28,117 --> 00:55:35,834
当我躺在地上时，大火已经赢得了战斗，周围是一圈人的身影。
When I came to lying on the ground, the fire had won the battle and all around was a ring of human figures.

730
00:55:35,917 --> 00:55:39,087
我抬头一看，它们被照亮了。
I looked up, they were illuminated.

731
00:55:39,170 --> 00:55:42,966
他们的眼睛，他们的牙齿像这样闪闪发光。
Their eyes, their teeth were shinin' like this.

732
00:55:43,049 --> 00:55:47,470
-对，像这样。-不，不要…不要……-像这样。-请别吓我。
- Yeah, like this. - No, don't... don't... - Like this. - Please don't scare me.

733
00:55:47,554 --> 00:55:50,598
我看到的面孔都在咧嘴笑。
The faces I saw were grinning.

734
00:55:50,682 --> 00:55:56,729
然后我知道，我知道火灾不是意外。
And then I knew, I knew the fire was not accidental.

735
00:55:56,813 --> 00:56:00,316
你也知道这不是偶然的。
And you know it was not accidental too.

736
00:56:00,400 --> 00:56:05,613
这是一种表达，一种需要毁灭的表现。
It was an expression, a manifestation of the need to destroy.

737
00:56:05,697 --> 00:56:16,541
